article.headline: Stetson 77, Mercer 68
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- E.J. Gordon and Anthony Register scored 18 points apiece to give Stetson a 77-68 win over Mercer on Thursday night, the Hatters' fifth consecutive victory. Kevin Craig added 17 points and seven rebounds for the Hatters (7-8, 5-4 Atlantic Sun Conference). Register scored 13 of his points in the second half, including going 7-of-8 from the free throw line in the final 2:43. Wesley Duke had 20 points, and Bobby Hansen added 17 for Mercer (7-11, 4-5). Gordon and Craig each scored 10 points in the first half as the Hatters built a 39-26 halftime lead. Mercer closed to within seven points early in the second half before the Hatters went on a 12-2 run to take a 53-36 lead. Mercer cut Stetson's lead to 62-54 on a dunk by Duke with 4:02 to play, but Gordon responded with two free throws and a dunk to push the lead back into double digits. It stayed that way until Hansen connected on a 3-pointer with six seconds left.
